 "text": "FBI and DHS reports show that 80% of terrorist incidents attributed to religious rhetoric are linked to organized extremist groups such as ISIS, al‑Qaeda, and the Taliban, whose operational plans are driven by ideological doctrines rather than by religious doctrine alone",
 "type": "empirical"
 },
 {
 "claim_id": 2,
 "text": "Scholarly analyses of religious texts (e.g., the Qur’an, the Bible, the Vedas) reveal no inherent call for violence; extremist interpretations are selective and distorted, indicating that the religion itself is not the cause of terrorism",
 "type": "scholarly"
 }
 ],
